http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Gas-pipeline-survey-works-in-Kannur-in-final-stage/article14000852.ece

The survey works for laying natural gas pipeline by Gas Authority of India Ltd (GAIL) in the district are in the final stage, according to GAIL officials.Speaking at a press conference here on Thursday, GAIL chief manager (corporate communications) Jyothi Kumar said that the survey has already covered 64 km of the total proposed pipeline length of 84 km in the district. He said Kannur was among the four districts where the works are set to enter the second phase, the others being Thrissur, Palakkad and Kasaragod.Efforts are now under way to accelerate the survey works in Kozhikode and Malappuram district, he said.